ipsecMIB.name: ipsecMIB
ipsecMIB.contactinfo: Newbridge Corporation 362 Terry Fox Drive Kanata, ON K0A 2H0 Canada 1-800-383-8211 tsupport@newbridge.com
ipsecMIB.description: The MIB module to describe generic IPSec objects, transient and permanent virtual tunnels created by IPSec SAs, and entity level IPSec objects and events.

ipsecIkeSaTable.name: ipsecIkeSaTable
ipsecIkeSaTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec's IKE SAs.

ipsecIkeSaEntry.name: ipsecIkeSaEntry
ipsecIkeSaEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IKE SA.

ipsecIkeSaIndex.name: ipsecIkeSaIndex
ipsecIkeSaIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each tunnel interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each tunnel interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of entity's network management system to the next re-initialization. Further, the value for tunnel interfaces that are marked as permanent must remain constant across all re- initializations of the network management system.

ipsecIkeSaPeerIpAddress.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerIpAddress
ipsecIkeSaPeerIpAddress.description: The IP address of the peer that this SA was negotiated with, or 0 if unknown.

ipsecIkeSaPeerPortNumber.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerPortNumber
ipsecIkeSaPeerPortNumber.description: The port number of the peer that this SA was negotiated with, or 0 if the default ISAKMP port number (500).

ipsecIkeSaAuthMethod.name: ipsecIkeSaAuthMethod
ipsecIkeSaAuthMethod.description: The authentication method used to authenticate the peers. Note that this does not include the specific method of authentication if extended authenticated is used. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Authentication Method from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaPeerIdType.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerIdType
ipsecIkeSaPeerIdType.description: The type of ID used by the peer. Specific values are used as described in Section 4.6.2.1 of [IPDOI].

ipsecIkeSaPeerId.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerId
ipsecIkeSaPeerId.description: The ID of the peer this SA was negotiated with. The length may require truncation under some conditions.

ipsecIkeSaPeerCertSerialNum.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerCertSerialNum
ipsecIkeSaPeerCertSerialNum.description: The serial number of the certificate of the peer this SA was negotiated with. This object has no meaning if a certificate was not used in authenticating the peer.

ipsecIkeSaPeerCertIssuer.name: ipsecIkeSaPeerCertIssuer
ipsecIkeSaPeerCertIssuer.description: The serial number of the certificate of the peer this SA was negotiated with. This object has no meaning if a certificate was not used in authenticating the peer.

ipsecIkeSaType.name: ipsecIkeSaType
ipsecIkeSaType.description: The type of virtual tunnel represented by this row. A transient link will disappear from the table when the SAs needed for it cannot be established. A permanent link will shows its status in the ipsecIkeSaStatus object.

ipsecIkeSaStatus.name: ipsecIkeSaStatus
ipsecIkeSaStatus.description: The status of the virtual tunnel represented by this row, if the tunnel is configured as permanent. 'neverTried' means that no attempt to set-up the link has been done. 'linkUp' means that the link is up and operating normally. 'linkDown' means that the link was up, but has gone down.

ipsecIkeSaEncAlg.name: ipsecIkeSaEncAlg
ipsecIkeSaEncAlg.description: A unique value representing the encryption algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA or 0 if there is no encryption applied. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Encryption Algorithms from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaEncKeyLength.name: ipsecIkeSaEncKeyLength
ipsecIkeSaEncKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for algorithm specified in the ipsecIkeSaEncAlg object or 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm or there is no encryption specified.

ipsecIkeSaHashAlg.name: ipsecIkeSaHashAlg
ipsecIkeSaHashAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA or 0 if there is no encryption applied. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Hash Algorithms from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupDesc.name: ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupDesc
ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupDesc.description: A unique value representing the Diffie-Hellman group description used or 0 if the group is unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Group Description from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupType.name: ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupType
ipsecIkeSaDifHelGroupType.description: A unique value representing the Diffie-Hellman group type used or 0 if the group is unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of Group Type from Appendix A of [IKE].

ipsecIkeSaDifHelFieldSize.name: ipsecIkeSaDifHelFieldSize
ipsecIkeSaDifHelFieldSize.description: The field size, in bits, of a Diffie-Hellman group.

ipsecIkeSaPRF.name: ipsecIkeSaPRF
ipsecIkeSaPRF.description: The pseudo-random functions used, or 0 if not used or if unknown. Specific values are used as described in the ISAKMP Class Values of PRF from Appendix A of [IKE] (which specifies none at the present time).

ipsecIkeSaPFS.name: ipsecIkeSaPFS
ipsecIkeSaPFS.description: A value that indicates that perfect forward secrecy is used for all IPSec SAs created by this IKE SA.

ipsecIkeSaInitiatorCookie.name: ipsecIkeSaInitiatorCookie
ipsecIkeSaInitiatorCookie.description: The value of the cookie used by the initiator for the current phase 1 SA.

ipsecIkeSaResponderCookie.name: ipsecIkeSaResponderCookie
ipsecIkeSaResponderCookie.description: The value of the cookie used by the responder for the current phase 1 SA.

ipsecIkeSaTimeStart.name: ipsecIkeSaTimeStart
ipsecIkeSaTimeStart.description: The date and time that the current SA within the link was set up. It is not the date and time that the virtual tunnel was set up.

ipsecIkeSaTimeLimit.name: ipsecIkeSaTimeLimit
ipsecIkeSaTimeLimit.description: The maximum lifetime in seconds of the current SA supporting the virtual tunnel, or 0 if there is no time constraint on its expiration.

ipsecIkeSaTrafficLimit.name: ipsecIkeSaTrafficLimit
ipsecIkeSaTrafficLimit.description: The maximum traffic in 1024-byte blocks that the current SA supporting the virtual tunnel is allowed to support, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration.

ipsecIkeSaInboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaInboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaInboundTraffic.description: The amount traffic measured in bytes handled in the current SA in the inbound direction.

ipsecIkeSaOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaOutboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaOutboundTraffic.description: The amount traffic measured in bytes handled in the current SA in the outbound direction.

ipsecIkeSaInboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaInboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaInboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled in the current SA in the inbound direction.

ipsecIkeSaOutboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaOutboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaOutboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled in the current SA in the outbound direction.

ipsecIkeSaTotalSaNum.name: ipsecIkeSaTotalSaNum
ipsecIkeSaTotalSaNum.description: The total number of SAs, including the current SA, that have been set up to support this virtual tunnel.

ipsecIkeSaFirstTimeStart.name: ipsecIkeSaFirstTimeStart
ipsecIkeSaFirstTimeStart.description: The data and time that this virtual tunnel was originally set up. It is not the time that the current SA was set up. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is reset when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaTotalInboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaTotalInboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaTotalInboundTraffic.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes handled in the tunnel in the inbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of all inbound traffic carried by all SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaTotalOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaTotalOutboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaTotalOutboundTraffic.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes handled in the tunnel in the outbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of all inbound traffic carried by all SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaTotalInboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaTotalInboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaTotalInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets handled by the virtual tunnel since it became active in the inbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of the number of inbound packets carried by all SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaTotalOutboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaTotalOutboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaTotalOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets handled by the virtual tunnel since it became active in the outbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of the number of outbound packets carried by all SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaDecryptErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaDecryptErrors
ipsecIkeSaDecryptErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets to this SA discarded due to decryption errors. Note that this refers to IKE protocol packets, and not to packets carried by SAs set up by the SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaHashErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaHashErrors
ipsecIkeSaHashErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets to this SA discarded due to hash errors. Note that this refers to IKE protocol packets, and not to packets carried by SAs set up by the SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecIkeSaOtherReceiveErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets to this SA discarded for reasons other than bad hashes or decryption errors. This may include packets dropped to a lack of receive buffer space. Note that this refers to IKE protocol packets, and not to packets carried by SAs set up by the SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaSendErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaSendErrors
ipsecIkeSaSendErrors.description: The total number of outbound packets from this SA discarded for any reason. This may include packets dropped to a lack of transmit buffer space. Note that this refers to IKE protocol packets, and not to packets carried by SAs set up by the SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecInboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecInboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaIpsecInboundTraffic.description: The total amount of inbound traffic measured in bytes handled by all IPSec SAs set up by phase 1 SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecOutboundTraffic
ipsecIkeSaIpsecOutboundTraffic.description: The total amount of outbound traffic measured in bytes handled by all IPSec SAs set up by phase 1 SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecInboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecInboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaIpsecInboundPackets.description: The total number of inbound packets handled by all IPSec SAs set up by phase 1 SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecOutboundPackets.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecOutboundPackets
ipsecIkeSaIpsecOutboundPackets.description: The total number of outbound packets handled by all IPSec SAs set up by phase 1 SAs supporting this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecDecryptErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecDecryptErrors
ipsecIkeSaIpsecDecryptErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by all IPSec SAs due to decryption errors. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecAuthErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecAuthErrors
ipsecIkeSaIpsecAuthErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by all IPSec SAs due to authentication errors. This includes hash failures in IPSec SAs using ESP and AH. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecReplayErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecReplayErrors
ipsecIkeSaIpsecReplayErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by all IPSec SAs due to replay errors. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecIkeSaIpsecOtherReceiveErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by all IPSec SAs due to errors other than authentication, decryption or replay errors. This may include packets dropped due to lack of receive buffers. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecIkeSaIpsecSendErrors.name: ipsecIkeSaIpsecSendErrors
ipsecIkeSaIpsecSendErrors.description: The total number of outbound packets discarded by all IPSec SAs due to any error. This may include packets dropped due to lack of receive buffers. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the tunnel goes to the 'linkUp' state.

ipsecTunnelTable.name: ipsecTunnelTable
ipsecTunnelTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec SA-based tunnels.

ipsecTunnelEntry.name: ipsecTunnelEntry
ipsecTunnelEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular configured tunnel.

ipsecTunnelIndex.name: ipsecTunnelIndex
ipsecTunnelIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each tunnel interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1. The value for each tunnel interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re-initialization. Further, the value for tunnel interfaces that are marked as permanent must remain constant across all re- initializations of the network management system.

ipsecTunnelIkeSa.name: ipsecTunnelIkeSa
ipsecTunnelIkeSa.description: The value of the index into the IKE SA tunnel table that created this tunnel (ipsecIkeSaIndex), or 0 if the tunnel is created by a static IPSec SA.

ipsecTunnelType.name: ipsecTunnelType
ipsecTunnelType.description: The type of the virtual tunnel represented by this row. 'static' means that the tunnel is supported by a single static IPSec SA that was setup by configuration, and not by using a key exchange protocol. In this case, the value of ipsecTunnelIkeSa must be 0.

ipsecTunnelLocalAddressOrStart.name: ipsecTunnelLocalAddressOrStart
ipsecTunnelLocalAddressOrStart.description: The address of or the start address (if an address range) of the local endpoint of the tunnel, or 0.0.0.0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

ipsecTunnelLocalAddressMaskOrEnd.name: ipsecTunnelLocalAddressMaskOrEnd
ipsecTunnelLocalAddressMaskOrEnd.description: The mask of or the end address (if an address range) of the local endpoint of the tunnel, or 0.0.0.0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

ipsecTunnelRemoteAddressOrStart.name: ipsecTunnelRemoteAddressOrStart
ipsecTunnelRemoteAddressOrStart.description: The address of or the start address (if an address range) of the remote endpoint of the tunnel, or 0.0.0.0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

ipsecTunnelRemoteAddressMaskOrEnd.name: ipsecTunnelRemoteAddressMaskOrEnd
ipsecTunnelRemoteAddressMaskOrEnd.description: The mask of or the end address (if an address range) of the remote endpoint of the tunnel, or 0.0.0.0 if unknown or if the SA uses transport mode encapsulation.

ipsecTunnelProtocol.name: ipsecTunnelProtocol
ipsecTunnelProtocol.description: The number of the protocol that this tunnel carries, or 0 if it carries any protocol.

ipsecTunnelLocalPort.name: ipsecTunnelLocalPort
ipsecTunnelLocalPort.description: The number of the local port that this tunnel carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecTunnelRemotePort.name: ipsecTunnelRemotePort
ipsecTunnelRemotePort.description: The number of the remote port that this tunnel carries, or 0 if it carries any port number.

ipsecTunnelMode.name: ipsecTunnelMode
ipsecTunnelMode.description: The type of encapsulation used by this virtual tunnel.

ipsecTunnelEspEncAlg.name: ipsecTunnelEspEncAlg
ipsecTunnelEspEncAlg.description: A unique value representing the encryption algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA if it uses ESP or 0 if there is no encryption applied by ESP or if ESP is not used. Specific values are taken from section 4.4.4 of [IPDOI].

ipsecTunnelEspEncKeyLength.name: ipsecTunnelEspEncKeyLength
ipsecTunnelEspEncKeyLength.description: The length of the encryption key in bits used for the algorithm specified in the ipsecTunnelEspEncAlg object, or 0 if the key length is implicit in the specified algorithm or there is no encryption specified.

ipsecTunnelEspAuthAlg.name: ipsecTunnelEspAuthAlg
ipsecTunnelEspAuthAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA if it uses ESP or 0 if there is no authentication applied by ESP or if ESP is not used. Specific values are taken from the Authentication Algorithm attribute values of Section 4.5 of [IPDOI].

ipsecTunnelAhAuthAlg.name: ipsecTunnelAhAuthAlg
ipsecTunnelAhAuthAlg.description: A unique value representing the hash algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA if it uses AH or 0 if AH is not used. Specific values are taken from Section 4.4.3 of [IPDOI].

ipsecTunnelCompAlg.name: ipsecTunnelCompAlg
ipsecTunnelCompAlg.description: A unique value representing the compression algorithm applied to traffic carried by this SA if it uses IPCOMP. Specific values are taken from Section 4.4.5 of [IPDOI].

ipsecTunnelStartTime.name: ipsecTunnelStartTime
ipsecTunnelStartTime.description: The date and time that this virtual tunnel was set up. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is reset when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum.name: ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum
ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum.description: The number of current SAs set up to support this virtual tunnel. If this number is 0, the tunnel must be considered down. Also if this number is 0, the tunnel must a permanent tunnel, since transient tunnels that are down do not appear in the table.

ipsecTunnelTotalSaNum.name: ipsecTunnelTotalSaNum
ipsecTunnelTotalSaNum.description: The total number of SAs, including all current SAs, that have been set up to support this virtual tunnel.

ipsecTunnelTotalInboundTraffic.name: ipsecTunnelTotalInboundTraffic
ipsecTunnelTotalInboundTraffic.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes handled in the tunnel in the inbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of all inbound traffic carried by all IPSec SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundTraffic
ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundTraffic.description: The total amount of traffic measured in bytes handled in the tunnel in the outbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of all inbound traffic carried by all IPSec SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelTotalInboundPackets.name: ipsecTunnelTotalInboundPackets
ipsecTunnelTotalInboundPackets.description: The total number of packets handled in the tunnel in the inbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of all inbound packets carried by all IPSec SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundPackets.name: ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundPackets
ipsecTunnelTotalOutboundPackets.description: The total number of packets handled in the tunnel in the outbound direction. In other words, it is the aggregate value of all outbound packets carried by all IPSec SAs ever set up to support the virtual tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelDecryptErrors.name: ipsecTunnelDecryptErrors
ipsecTunnelDecryptErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by this virtual tunnel due to decryption errors in ESP. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelAuthErrors.name: ipsecTunnelAuthErrors
ipsecTunnelAuthErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by this virtual tunnel due to authentication errors. This includes hash failures in IPSec SA bundles using both ESP and AH. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not resetto zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelReplayErrors.name: ipsecTunnelReplayErrors
ipsecTunnelReplayErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by this virtual tunnel due to replay errors. This includes replay failures in IPSec SA bundles using both ESP and AH. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelPolicyErrors.name: ipsecTunnelPolicyErrors
ipsecTunnelPolicyErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by this virtual tunnel due to policy errors. This includes errors in all transforms if SA bundles are used. Policy errors are due to the detection of a packet that was inappropriately sent into this tunnel. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecTunnelOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecTunnelOtherReceiveErrors.description: The total number of inbound packets discarded by this virtual tunnel due to errors other than decryption, authentication or replay errors. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of receive buffers. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecTunnelSendErrors.name: ipsecTunnelSendErrors
ipsecTunnelSendErrors.description: The total number of outbound packets discarded by this virtual tunnel due to any error. This may include packets dropped due to a lack of transmit buffers. If this is a permanent virtual tunnel, it is not reset to zero when the number of current SAs (ipsecTunnelCurrentSaNum) changes from 0 to 1.

ipsecSaTable.name: ipsecSaTable
ipsecSaTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec SAs.

ipsecSaEntry.name: ipsecSaEntry
ipsecSaEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the information on a particular IPSec SA.

ipsecSaIndex.name: ipsecSaIndex
ipsecSaIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each IPSec SA. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

ipsecSaTunnel.name: ipsecSaTunnel
ipsecSaTunnel.description: The value of the index into the IPSec SA tunnel table that this SA supports (ipsecTunnelIndex).

ipsecSaInboundEspSpi.name: ipsecSaInboundEspSpi
ipsecSaInboundEspSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the inbound SA that provides the ESP security service, or zero if ESP is not used.

ipsecSaOutboundEspSpi.name: ipsecSaOutboundEspSpi
ipsecSaOutboundEspSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the outbound SA that provides the ESP security service, or zero if ESP is not used.

ipsecSaInboundAhSpi.name: ipsecSaInboundAhSpi
ipsecSaInboundAhSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the inbound SA that provides the AH security service, or zero if AH is not used.

ipsecSaOutboundAhSpi.name: ipsecSaOutboundAhSpi
ipsecSaOutboundAhSpi.description: The value of the SPI for the outbound SA that provides the AH security service, or zero if AH is not used.

ipsecSaInboundCompCpi.name: ipsecSaInboundCompCpi
ipsecSaInboundCompCpi.description: The value of the CPI for the inbound SA that provides IP compression, or zero if IPCOMP is not used.

ipsecSaOutboundCompCpi.name: ipsecSaOutboundCompCpi
ipsecSaOutboundCompCpi.description: The value of the CPI for the outbound SA that provides IP compression, or zero if IPCOMP is not used.

ipsecSaCreationTime.name: ipsecSaCreationTime
ipsecSaCreationTime.description: The date and time that the current SA was set up.

ipsecSaTimeLimit.name: ipsecSaTimeLimit
ipsecSaTimeLimit.description: The maximum lifetime in seconds of the SA, or 0 if there is no time constraint on its expiration.

ipsecSaTrafficLimit.name: ipsecSaTrafficLimit
ipsecSaTrafficLimit.description: The maximum traffic in 1024-byte blocks that the SA is allowed to support, or 0 if there is no traffic constraint on its expiration.

ipsecSaInboundTraffic.name: ipsecSaInboundTraffic
ipsecSaInboundTraffic.description: The amount traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA in the inbound direction.

ipsecSaOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecSaOutboundTraffic
ipsecSaOutboundTraffic.description: The amount traffic measured in bytes handled by the SA in the outbound direction.

ipsecSaInboundPackets.name: ipsecSaInboundPackets
ipsecSaInboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA in the inbound direction.

ipsecSaOutboundPackets.name: ipsecSaOutboundPackets
ipsecSaOutboundPackets.description: The number of packets handled by the SA in the outbound direction.

ipsecSaDecryptErrors.name: ipsecSaDecryptErrors
ipsecSaDecryptErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the SA due to decryption errors.

ipsecSaAuthErrors.name: ipsecSaAuthErrors
ipsecSaAuthErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the SA due to authentication errors. This includes hash failures in both ESP and AH.

ipsecSaReplayErrors.name: ipsecSaReplayErrors
ipsecSaReplayErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the SA due to replay errors. This includes replay failures both ESP and AH.

ipsecSaOtherReceiveErrors.name: ipsecSaOtherReceiveErrors
ipsecSaOtherReceiveErrors.description: The number of inbound packets discarded by the SA due to errors other than decryption, authentication or replay errors. This may include decompression errors or errors due to a lack of receive buffers.

ipsecSaSendErrors.name: ipsecSaSendErrors
ipsecSaSendErrors.description: The number of outbound packets discarded by the SA due to any error. This may include compression errors or errors due to a lack of transmit buffers.

ipsecTotalIkeSAs.name: ipsecTotalIkeSAs
ipsecTotalIkeSAs.description: The total number of phase 1 SAs established by the entity since boot time. It is not the total number of tunnels established by the entity since boot time. It does include SAs established to support both permanent and transient tunnels.

ipsecTotalIpsecSAs.name: ipsecTotalIpsecSAs
ipsecTotalIpsecSAs.description: The total number of phase 2 SAs established by the entity since boot time. It is not the total number of IPSec virtual tunnels established by the entity since boot time. It does include SAs established to support permanent and transient tunnels. It is recommended that SA bundles or security suites be considered a single SA for the purposes of this statistic.

ipsecCnfgPermIkeTunnels.name: ipsecCnfgPermIkeTunnels
ipsecCnfgPermIkeTunnels.description: The total number of phase 1 tunnels in the entity that are configured as permanent.

ipsecUpPermIkeTunnels.name: ipsecUpPermIkeTunnels
ipsecUpPermIkeTunnels.description: The total number of phase 1 tunnels in the entity that are configured as permanent and are up and available for use.

ipsecCnfgPermIpsecTunnels.name: ipsecCnfgPermIpsecTunnels
ipsecCnfgPermIpsecTunnels.description: The total number of phase 2 tunnels in the entity that are configured as permanent.

ipsecUpPermIpsecTunnels.name: ipsecUpPermIpsecTunnels
ipsecUpPermIpsecTunnels.description: The total number of phase 2 tunnels in the entity that are configured as permanent and are up and available for use.

ipsecTotalTransIkeTunnels.name: ipsecTotalTransIkeTunnels
ipsecTotalTransIkeTunnels.description: The total number of transient phase 1 tunnels established by the entity since boot time.

ipsecCurrentTransIkeTunnels.name: ipsecCurrentTransIkeTunnels
ipsecCurrentTransIkeTunnels.description: The number of transient phase 1 tunnels in the entity that are up and available for use at this moment in time.

ipsecTotalTransIpsecTunnels.name: ipsecTotalTransIpsecTunnels
ipsecTotalTransIpsecTunnels.description: The total number of transient phase 2 tunnels established by the entity since boot time.

ipsecCurrentTransIpsecTunnels.name: ipsecCurrentTransIpsecTunnels
ipsecCurrentTransIpsecTunnels.description: The number of phase 2 tunnels in the entity that are up and available for use at this moment in time.

ipsecTotalTransInboundPackets.name: ipsecTotalTransInboundPackets
ipsecTotalTransInboundPackets.description: The total number of inbound packets carried on transient IPSec tunnels since boot time.

ipsecTotalTransOutboundPackets.name: ipsecTotalTransOutboundPackets
ipsecTotalTransOutboundPackets.description: The total number of outbound packets carried on transient IPSec tunnels since boot time.

ipsecTotalTransInboundTraffic.name: ipsecTotalTransInboundTraffic
ipsecTotalTransInboundTraffic.description: The total amount of inbound traffic carried on transient IPSec tunnels since boot time, measured in 1024-octet blocks.

ipsecTotalTransOutboundTraffic.name: ipsecTotalTransOutboundTraffic
ipsecTotalTransOutboundTraffic.description: The total amount of outbound traffic carried on transient IPSec tunnels since boot time, measured in 1024-octet blocks.

ipsecTotalTransIkeSetupFailures.name: ipsecTotalTransIkeSetupFailures
ipsecTotalTransIkeSetupFailures.description: The total number of IKE SA set up attempts that have failed since entity boot time. This includes SAs associated with transient tunnels only.

ipsecUnknownSpiErrors.name: ipsecUnknownSpiErrors
ipsecUnknownSpiErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with SPIs or CPIs that were not valid.

ipsecIkeProtocolErrors.name: ipsecIkeProtocolErrors
ipsecIkeProtocolErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with IKE protocol errors. This includes packets with invalid cookies, but does not include errors that could be associated with specific IKE SAs.

ipsecIpsecAuthenticationErrors.name: ipsecIpsecAuthenticationErrors
ipsecIpsecAuthenticationErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with authentication errors in the IPSec SAs. This includes all packets in which the hash value is determined to be invalid.

ipsecIpsecReplayErrors.name: ipsecIpsecReplayErrors
ipsecIpsecReplayErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time with replay errors in the IPSec SAs.

ipsecIpsecPolicyErrors.name: ipsecIpsecPolicyErrors
ipsecIpsecPolicyErrors.description: The total number of packets received by the entity since boot time and discarded due to policy errors. This includes packets that had selectors that were invalid for the SA that carried them.

ipsecNotifyMessageTotalCount.name: ipsecNotifyMessageTotalCount
ipsecNotifyMessageTotalCount.description: The total number of all types of notify messages sent or received by the entity since boot time. It is the sum of all occurrences in the 'ipsecNotifyCountTable'.

ipsecNotifyCountTable.name: ipsecNotifyCountTable
ipsecNotifyCountTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on IPSec notify message counts. This table MAY be sparsely populated; that is, rows for which the count is 0 may be absent.

ipsecNotifyCountEntry.name: ipsecNotifyCountEntry
ipsecNotifyCountEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the total number of occurrences of a notify message.

ipsecNotifyMessage.name: ipsecNotifyMessage
ipsecNotifyMessage.description: The value representing a specific IPSec notify message, or 0 if unknown. Values are assigned from the set of notify message types as defined in Section 3.14.1 of [ISAKMP]. In addition, the value 0 may be used for this object when the object is used as a trap cause, and the cause is unknown.

ipsecNotifyMessageCount.name: ipsecNotifyMessageCount
ipsecNotifyMessageCount.description: The total number of times the specific notify message has been received or sent by the entity since system boot.

ipsecTrapPermIkeNegFailure.name: ipsecTrapPermIkeNegFailure
ipsecTrapPermIkeNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 1 SA for the specified permanent IKE tunnel failed.

ipsecTrapTransIkeNegFailure.name: ipsecTrapTransIkeNegFailure
ipsecTrapTransIkeNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 1 SA for a transient IKE tunnel failed. This trap is different from the 'ipsecTrapPermIkeNegFailure' trap, since this one will likely result in the removal of this entry from the IKE SA tunnel table.

ipsecTrapInvalidCookie.name: ipsecTrapInvalidCookie
ipsecTrapInvalidCookie.description: IKE packets with invalid cookies were detected from the specified peer. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period, rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapIpsecNegFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecNegFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecNegFailure.description: An attempt to negotiate a phase 2 SA within the specified IKE tunnel failed.

ipsecTrapIpsecAuthFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecAuthFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecAuthFailure.description: IPSec packets with invalid hashes were found in the specified SA. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapIpsecReplayFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecReplayFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecReplayFailure.description: IPSec packets with invalid sequence numbers were found in the specified SA. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapIpsecPolicyFailure.name: ipsecTrapIpsecPolicyFailure
ipsecTrapIpsecPolicyFailure.description: IPSec packets carrying packets with invalid selectors for the specified SA were found. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per SA (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.

ipsecTrapInvalidSpi.name: ipsecTrapInvalidSpi
ipsecTrapInvalidSpi.description: ESP, AH or IPCOMP packets with unknown SPIs (or CPIs) were detected from the specified peer. Implementations SHOULD send one trap per peer (within a reasonable time period), rather than sending one trap per packet.
